  "description": "Per-client (host) statistics for Pure FlashArrays. Host stats are aggregate across all transports \u2014 no per-protocol/NVMe split exists.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 0,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "liveNow": false,
  "panels": [
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Per-client visibility \u2014 what we can and can't see",
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Host stats below are **aggregate across all transports** (FC / iSCSI / NVMe-TCP / NVMe-FC). No `protocol`, `nqn`, or `transport` label exists on any host metric, so **NVMe traffic cannot be isolated per client.**\n\n**We see (per host):** IOPS, bandwidth, latency, avg IO size, space, data reduction, host\u2192volume connections, connectivity status.\n\n**We don't see (per host):** which transport carries the traffic, per-NVMe-client throughput, NVMe session counts.\n\n_Pick a client in the **Host** dropdown for the detail row. Target-side NVMe/TCP visibility lives in the **Pure FlashArray \u00b7 NVMe/TCP** dashboard._"
      }
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
